        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 5:40PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 539 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Marion, moving west at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marion, Gas City, Jonesboro, Sweetser, Swayzee, Van Buren, Sims,
Converse, Home Corner, Landess, Michaelsville, Normal, Mier, Jalapa,
Herbst, Hanfield, Point Isabel, Radley, Roseburg, and Lake Wood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
